  Computers are available to students, residents, faculty, staff and visitors in the public area of the Library. The Library Learning Lab is available 24/7 to students, residents, faculty and staff, using their UIC icard.    Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria             Visitor services    All library locations are open to anyone, though some restrictions apply if you are not affiliated with UIC. Visitors can use books and other materials and services (such as research help) in person during most of the hours the library locations are open.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Check out a laptop    Laptop checkouts are available to students in Urbana, Peoria and both Chicago libraries.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Connect to wifi at the library    All library locations offer wireless for students, faculty, staff and visitors.    Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Use assistive technologies    The Library has adjustable tables, screen reader software and computer screen magnification software installed on computers in each building.    Richard J. Daley Library  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana          Filter by Location     Chicago-Daley     Chicago-Health Sciences     Peoria-Health Sciences     Rockford-Health Sciences     Urbana-Health Sciences     Apply filters     Filter by Topic     Accessibility     Borrowing     Computers, Printing & Scanning     Copyright & Scholarly Publishing     Cours